clinical_study.brief_title: Follow-up Study of L059 (Levetiracetam) in Epileptic Patients With Partial Onset Seizures by Open Label Method
clinical_study.official_title: Follow-up Study of L059 (Levetiracetam) in Epileptic Patients With Partial Onset Seizures by Open Label Method

brief_summary.textblock: The safety and efficacy of L059 was evaluated in patients who completed "N165 Clinical Trial of L059". They received L059 at a daily dose from 1,000 mg to 3,000 mg in addition to their standard concomitant AEDs

study_design_info.intervention_model_description: This study N01020 (NCT00160615) was designed as a single group assignment study and as follow-up study, open for patients from N165 (NCT00600509). The differentiation into placebo and Levetiracetam in the results reporting section is based on the treatment of the previously conducted study N165 (NCT00600509).

arm_group.description: Subjects received oral tablets of Levetiracetam. This study N01020 (NCT00160615) was designed as a single group assignment study and as follow-up study, open for patients from N165 (NCT00600509). The differentiation into placebo and Levetiracetam in the results reporting section is based on the treatment of the previously conducted study N165 (NCT00600509).

intervention.description: Pharmaceutical form: Film-coating tablets Concentration: 250 mg/ 500 mg Route of administration: oral use

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Patients who completed the evaluation period (Week 16) of N165 Clinical Trial of L059
- Patients/the parent or guardian wish to continue treatment with L059 and to enter N165 Follow-up Study, and also the investigator admit the necessity of the repeated intake of the investigational drug for the patients.
Exclusion Criteria:
- Patients who had not participate in N165 Clinical Trial of L059.
- Patients who had participated in N165 Clinical Trial of L059 with no intention of entering the follow-up study taking the same medication.
- Patients had not been in compliance with requirements of Protocol for N165 Clinical Trial of L059 in the course of the study.

participant_flow.recruitment_details: The study started to enroll patients in September 2001 and concluded in January 2007.
participant_flow.pre_assignment_details: Participant Flow refers to the Full Analysis Set (FAS). Of the 154 subjects who enrolled in the study, 151 subjects were included in the FAS population and 3 subjects were identified with major protocol deviations leading to exclusion from FAS.

group.title: N165 Randomized Treatment PBO
group.description: Subjects received Placebo (PBO) in study N165 [NCT00600509] and received LEV in this study: After starting with the 4 week-fixed 3000 mg/day, the daily doses of LEV were permitted to be adjusted by 500 or 1000 mg/day at a 4-week interval between 1000 mg/day and 3000 mg/day.

group.description: Subjects received Levetiracetam (LEV) in study N165 [NCT00600509] and received LEV in this study: After starting with the 4 week-fixed 3000 mg/day, the daily doses of LEV were permitted to be adjusted by 500 or 1000 mg/day at a 4-week interval between 1000 mg/day and 3000 mg/day.

reported_events.desc: Adverse events refer to the Full Analysis Set (FAS).

group.title: N165 Randomized Treatment PBO (FAS)
group.description: Subjects received Placebo (PBO) in study N165 [NCT00600509] and received LEV in this study: After starting with the 4 week-fixed 3000 mg/day, the daily doses of LEV were permitted to be adjusted by 500 or 1000 mg/day at a 4-week interval between 1000 mg/day and 3000 mg/day. In the Placebo group the Serious Adverse Events (SAEs) Status epilepticus and Agitation occurred twice in 2 subjects.

certain_agreements.pi_employee: Principal Investigators are NOT employed by the organization sponsoring the study.
certain_agreements.restrictive_agreement: The only disclosure restriction on the PI is that the sponsor can review results communications prior to public release and can embargo communications regarding trial results for a period that is more than 60 days but less than or equal to 180 days. The sponsor cannot require changes to the communication and cannot extend the embargo.
